#### Pro Tips

1. The Opera Mini Simulator is a great tool
1. Screen shots from (all versions of) Android? Do this:
    1. Install the Android SDK
    1. Make sure to install `platform-tools`
    1. Connect the Android device in question to USB
    1. In the Android SDK directory, find `ddms` under `tools` and launch it (You can also run `ddms` from a Terminal window in most Android SDK installs).
    1. Find the connected device in the `Dalvik Debug Monitor` window and use Device -> Capture Screen... to do a screen grab. [Here's a screenshot](images/ddms.png).



